[Sheng Siong is the 3rd largest chain of supermarkets in Singapore (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sheng_Siong).

A report mistakenly said that listeriosis in a hospitalized patient at Singapore General Hospital was linked to eating a melon, but the melon was called a Hami melon, which is a type of muskmelon, originally from Hami, Xinjiang, China. This report was in Chinese and machine translated (https://www.channel8news.sg/news8/singapore/2080309-sg-sgh-listeria/3977428.html). Pictures of Hami melons are available at: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hami_melon.

Singapore recalled all rockmelons [cantaloupes] imported from Australia as a "precautionary measure" several days ago in response to the outbreak in Australia that had been traced to a specific grower in the Australian state of New South Wales, No cases of listeriosis have been linked to consumption of Australian rockmelons in Singapore.

Singapore is an island nation in Southeast Asia at the southern tip of the Malay Peninsula, with Indonesia to the south. A map of Singapore can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Singapore. - Mod.ML

